==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sexton
<hw>Sex"ton</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>sextein</ets>, contr. fr. <ets>sacristan</ets>.]</ety> <def>An
under officer of a church, whose business is to take care of the church
building and the vessels, vestments, etc., belonging to the church, to
attend on the officiating clergyman, and to perform other duties
pertaining to the church, such as to dig graves, ring the bell,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sexton beetle</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a burying
beetle.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sextoness</ent>⟦br⟧
